Alzheimer's brain plaques and tangles linked        22:00 28 July 03     NewScientist.com news service      urlLink http://www.newscientist.com/news/news.jsp?id=ns99993992   A causal link between plaques and tangles, the two pathological hallmarks of brains ravaged by Alzheimer's disease, has been shown for the first time, researchers claim.  In the new study, the scientists found that the protein found in plaques can initiate a process that damages other proteins inside cells and makes them vulnerable to tangling. "This is a new, direct linkage" between plaques and tangles, says Vincent Cryns, who conducted the research with Lester Binder and others at Northwestern University in Illinois.  for more...  urlLink http://www.newscientist.com/news/news.jsp?id=ns99993992